**Crew Supervisor -- FIFO Role in Central QLD (Projects Team)**

**Position**: Crew Supervisor (Projects Team)\
**Location**: FIFO (Fly In, Fly Out) to a Hard Rock Mine Site located in
Central Queensland\
**Roster**: 8/6 Roster\
**Job Type**: Casual

**About the Role**\
We are looking for a highly motivated and experienced Crew Supervisor to
join our Projects Team on a mining project in Central Queensland. In
this role, you will lead and manage a skilled team of workers to ensure
the successful execution of project-specific tasks while adhering to
safety, quality, and productivity standards. As part of the Projects
Team, your leadership will be key to meeting project milestones and
ensuring operations are carried out efficiently and effectively.

**Key Responsibilities**

-   Supervise and coordinate the daily activities of a crew working on
    project-specific mining operations in a timely manner.

-   Lead a small team to complete tasks safely, on time, and within
    budget.

-   Ensure compliance with safety procedures, environmental standards,
    and operational requirements throughout project execution.

-   Allocate tasks and resources efficiently to optimise productivity
    and meet project deadlines.

-   Foster a positive, collaborative work environment through effective
    leadership and communication.

-   Conduct regular safety briefings, toolbox talks, and maintain high
    safety standards and team morale.

-   Monitor progress against project plans, adjusting team activities
    and resources to address any challenges.

-   Report on team performance, safety issues, and operational concerns
    to project managers and senior leadership.

-   Identify and resolve operational issues, including equipment
    failures, safety hazards, and resource constraints, in a timely
    manner.

**Skills and Experience**

-   Minimum 5 years of experience in mining.

-   Previous experience as a Crew Supervisor or similar leadership role
    in mining, heavy industry, or construction projects.

-   Strong leadership and team management skills, with the ability to
    motivate and support crew members.

-   Solid understanding of mining operations, including project-based
    work.

-   Proven ability to manage teams in a remote site environment and meet
    project-specific goals.

-   In-depth knowledge of safety regulations, environmental compliance,
    and risk management.

-   Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability
    to collaborate effectively.

-   Strong problem-solving abilities, with a focus on resolving
    operational and safety challenges.

-   Relevant qualifications or certifications in mining, project
    supervision, or leadership (e.g., RII certifications, Supervisor
    Training).

